' Parametric leaf antenna generator for CST Studio Suite 2025
' Units: mm, GHz
'
' Usage:
'   1. Open a new CST Microwave Studio project.
'   2. Macro > Visual Basic > Open this file > Run.
'   3. Tune parameters in CST's parameter list, then rerun this macro to rebuild.
'
' Main sweep parameter:
'   num_fin_pairs      Number of fins. In alternating mode this is individual fins; in mirrored mode this is fin pairs.
'
' Useful tuning parameters:
'   leaf_length        Tip-to-base leaf length.
'   leaf_height        Maximum leaf width.
'   rim_width          Width of the outer leaf rim.
'   metal_thickness    Copper thickness, default 1 mm from the drawing.
'   center_stem_width  Width of the center conductor/stem.
'   fin_layout_mode    1 = center-out mirrored fin pairs, 0 = legacy evenly spaced mirrored fin pairs.
'   fin_len_1..8       Individual fin/vein lengths.
'   fin_angle_1..8     Individual fin/vein angles in degrees from +X.
'   fin_end_angle      Slanted cap angle at each fin end.
'   fin_end_len        Length of the slanted cap at each fin end.
'   leaf_base_spline_gap    Centerline gap where the rim starts at the feed/stem side.
'   rim_tip_to_tip_length Vertical distance between the two rim/spline tips.
'   rim_over_stem     How far the upper rim tip extends past the main stem.
'   rim_end_gap        Clear gap between rim inner edges at the opposite end.
'   rim_curve_bias     Shape exponent for the native CST rim spline arc.
'   rim_stem_clearance      Extra clearance between the center stem and outer rim starts.
'   rim_spline_points  Number of points used to define each native CST rim spline.
'   unite_radiator_all Boolean-unite all radiator solids at the end; ground remains separate.
'   trim_fin_stem_overlap Trim fin/vein overlap volume using the main stem as a mask.
'   trim_rim_stem_overlap Trim outer rim/spline overlap volume using the main stem as a mask.
'   trim_rim_feed_overlap Trim outer rim/spline overlap volume using the feed as a mask.
'   vein_rim_clearance Extra clearance from fin/vein ends to the inner rim.
'   vein_stem_overlap  Electrical/mechanical overlap between each vein and the main stem.
'   ground_size        Square ground-plane side length.
'   leaf_ground_gap    Air gap between radiator/feed bottom and ground top.
'   use_tetrahedral_mesh Use tetra/surface-style mesh display instead of forcing PBA mesh planes.
'
' Assumptions in this first model:
'   - The leaf radiator is a 1 mm thick copper solid standing upright in the YZ plane.
'   - The 60 x 60 mm ground plane is horizontal in the XY plane below the feed end.
'   - The SMA is represented as a 50 ohm discrete port from feed to ground.
'   - Geometry is made from short copper brick segments so vein count can be
'     regenerated by the macro without relying on imported DXF topology.

Option Explicit

Const PI As Double = 3.1415926535897931
Dim RadiatorObjects As String
Dim FinObjects As String
Dim RimObjects As String

Sub Main()
    InitProject
    EnsureParameters
    If CInt(P("use_dxf_defaults")) <> 0 Then ApplyDxfDefaults
    RebuildLeafAntenna
    SetupSimulation
End Sub

Sub InitProject()
    With Units
        .Geometry "mm"
        .Frequency "GHz"
        .Time "ns"
    End With

    On Error Resume Next
    Component.Delete "Radiator"
    Component.Delete "Ground"
    Component.Delete "TrimMasks"
    On Error GoTo 0

    Component.New "Radiator"
    Component.New "Ground"
    DefineCopperAnnealed
End Sub

